169  static FILE *_internalFileOpener(const char *fn, const char *mode)
170  {
171  FILE *fp = nullptr;
172 
173  #ifndef WIN32
174  fp = fopen(fn, mode);
175  #else
176  if(fopen_s(&fp, fn, mode) != 0)
177  {
178  fp = nullptr;
179  }
180  #endif
181 
182  return fp;
183  }
184 
185  #define JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(_cn) \
186  class _cn; \
187  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const _cn& p); \
188  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, _cn& p);
189 
190  #define IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(_cn) \
191  public: \
192  static void document(const char *path = nullptr) \
193  { \
194  _cn example; \
195  example.initForDocumenting(); \
196  std::string theJson = example.serialize(3); \
197  std::cout << "------------------------------------------------" << std::endl \
198  << #_cn << std::endl \
199  << theJson << std::endl \
200  << "------------------------------------------------" << std::endl; \
201  \
202  if(path != nullptr && path[0] != 0) \
203  { \
204  std::string fn = path; \
205  fn.append("/"); \
206  fn.append(#_cn); \
207  fn.append(".json"); \
208  \
209  FILE *fp = _internalFileOpener(fn.c_str(), "wt");\
210  \
211  if(fp != nullptr) \
212  { \
213  fputs(theJson.c_str(), fp); \
214  fclose(fp); \
215  } \
216  else \
217  { \
218  std::cout << "ERROR: Cannot write to " << fn << std::endl; \
219  } \
220  } \
221  }
222 
223  #define IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION() \
224  public: \
225  bool deserialize(const char *s) \
226  { \
227  try \
228  { \
229  if(s != nullptr && s[0] != 0) \
230  { \
231  from_json(nlohmann::json::parse(s), *this); \
232  } \
233  else \
234  { \
235  return false; \
236  } \
237  } \
238  catch(...) \
239  { \
240  return false; \
241  } \
242  return true; \
243  } \
244  \
245  std::string serialize(const int indent = -1) \
246  { \
247  nlohmann::json j; \
248  to_json(j, *this); \
249  return j.dump(indent); \
250  }
251 
252  #define IMPLEMENT_WRAPPED_JSON_SERIALIZATION(_cn) \
253  public: \
254  std::string serializeWrapped(const int indent = -1) \
255  { \
256  nlohmann::json j; \
257  to_json(j, *this); \
258  \
259  std::string rc; \
260  char firstChar[2]; \
261  firstChar[0] = #_cn[0]; \
262  firstChar[1] = 0; \
263  firstChar[0] = tolower(firstChar[0]); \
264  rc.assign("{\""); \
265  rc.append(firstChar); \
266  rc.append((#_cn) + 1); \
267  rc.append("\":"); \
268  rc.append(j.dump(indent)); \
269  rc.append("}"); \
270  \
271  return rc; \
272  }
273 
274  #define TOJSON_IMPL(__var) \
275  {#__var, p.__var}
276 
277  #define FROMJSON_IMPL_SIMPLE(__var) \
278  getOptional(#__var, p.__var, j)
279 
280  #define FROMJSON_IMPL(__var, __type, __default) \
281  getOptional<__type>(#__var, p.__var, j, __default)

285  static std::string EMPTY_STRING;
286 
287  template<class T>
288  static void getOptional(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, T def)
289  {
290  try
291  {
292  if(j.contains(name))
293  {
294  j.at(name).get_to(v);
295  }
296  else
297  {
298  v = def;
299  }
300  }
301  catch(...)
302  {
303  v = def;
304  }
305  }
306 
307  template<class T>
308  static void getOptional(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j)
309  {
310  try
311  {
312  if(j.contains(name))
313  {
314  j.at(name).get_to(v);
315  }
316  }
317  catch(...)
318  {
319  }
320  }
321 
322  template<class T>
323  static void getOptionalWithIndicator(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, T def, bool *wasFound)
324  {
325  try
326  {
327  if(j.contains(name))
328  {
329  j.at(name).get_to(v);
330  *wasFound = true;
331  }
332  else
333  {
334  v = def;
335  *wasFound = false;
336  }
337  }
338  catch(...)
339  {
340  v = def;
341  *wasFound = false;
342  }
343  }
344 
345  template<class T>
346  static void getOptionalWithIndicator(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, bool *wasFound)
347  {
348  try
349  {
350  if(j.contains(name))
351  {
352  j.at(name).get_to(v);
353  *wasFound = true;
354  }
355  else
356  {
357  *wasFound = false;
358  }
359  }
360  catch(...)
361  {
362  *wasFound = false;
363  }
364  }

366  class ConfigurationObjectBase
367  {
368  public:
369  ConfigurationObjectBase()
370  {
371  _documenting = false;
372  }
373 
374  virtual ~ConfigurationObjectBase()
375  {
376  }
377 
378  virtual void initForDocumenting()
379  {
380  _documenting = true;
381  }
382 
383  virtual std::string toString()
384  {
385  return std::string("");
386  }
387 
388  inline virtual bool isDocumenting() const
389  {
390  return _documenting;
391  }
392 
393  protected:
394  bool _documenting;
395  };

400  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(WatchdogSettings)
401  class WatchdogSettings : public ConfigurationObjectBase
402  {
403  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
404  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(WatchdogSettings)
405 
406  public:
408  bool enabled;
409 
411  int intervalMs;
412 
414  int hangDetectionMs;
415 
417  bool abortOnHang;
418 
420  int slowExecutionThresholdMs;
421 
422  WatchdogSettings()
423  {
424  clear();
425  }
426 
427  void clear()
428  {
429  enabled = true;
430  intervalMs = 5000;
431  hangDetectionMs = 2000;
432  abortOnHang = true;
433  slowExecutionThresholdMs = 100;
434  }
435 
436  virtual void initForDocumenting()
437  {
438  clear();
439  }
440  };
441 
442  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const WatchdogSettings& p)
443  {
444  j = nlohmann::json{
445  TOJSON_IMPL(enabled),
446  TOJSON_IMPL(intervalMs),
447  TOJSON_IMPL(hangDetectionMs),
448  TOJSON_IMPL(abortOnHang),
449  TOJSON_IMPL(slowExecutionThresholdMs)
450  };
451  }
452  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, WatchdogSettings& p)
453  {
454  p.clear();
455  getOptional<bool>("enabled", p.enabled, j, true);
456  getOptional<int>("intervalMs", p.intervalMs, j, 5000);
457  getOptional<int>("hangDetectionMs", p.hangDetectionMs, j, 2000);
458  getOptional<bool>("abortOnHang", p.abortOnHang, j, true);
459  getOptional<int>("slowExecutionThresholdMs", p.slowExecutionThresholdMs, j, 100);
460  }

519 
520  public:
521  std::string id;
522  std::string name;
523  std::string description;
524  std::string comments;
525  int count;
526  int used; // NOTE: Ignored during deserialization!
527 
528  Feature()
529  {
530  clear();
531  }
532 
533  void clear()
534  {
535  id.clear();
536  name.clear();
537  description.clear();
538  comments.clear();
539  count = 0;
540  used = 0;
541  }
542 
543  virtual void initForDocumenting()
544  {
545  clear();
546  id = "{af9540d1-3e86-4fa6-8b80-e26daecb61ab}";
547  name = "A sample feature";
548  description = "This is an example of a feature";
549  comments = "These are comments for this feature";
550  count = 42;
551  used = 16;
552  }
553  };
554 
555  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Feature& p)
556  {
557  j = nlohmann::json{
558  TOJSON_IMPL(id),
559  TOJSON_IMPL(name),
560  TOJSON_IMPL(description),
561  TOJSON_IMPL(comments),
562  TOJSON_IMPL(count),
563  TOJSON_IMPL(used)
564  };
565  }
566  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Feature& p)
567  {
568  p.clear();
569  j.at("id").get_to(p.id);
570  getOptional("name", p.name, j);
571  getOptional("description", p.description, j);
572  getOptional("comments", p.comments, j);
573  getOptional("count", p.count, j, 0);
574 
575  // NOTE: Not deserialized!
576  //getOptional("used", p.used, j, 0);
577  }

715  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(RtpPayloadTypeTranslation)
716 
717  public:
719  uint16_t external;
720 
722  uint16_t engage;
723 
724  RtpPayloadTypeTranslation()
725  {
726  clear();
727  }
728 
729  void clear()
730  {
731  external = 0;
732  engage = 0;
733  }
734 
735  bool matches(const RtpPayloadTypeTranslation& other)
736  {
737  return ( (external == other.external) && (engage == other.engage) );
738  }
739  };
740

742  {

745  TOJSON_IMPL(engage)
746  };
747  }

749  {
750  p.clear();
751  getOptional<uint16_t>("external", p.external, j);
752  getOptional<uint16_t>("engage", p.engage, j);
753  }

881  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(RtpHeader)
882 
883  public:
884 
886  int pt;
887 
889  bool marker;
890 
892  uint16_t seq;
893 
895  uint32_t ssrc;
896 
898  uint32_t ts;
899 
900  RtpHeader()
901  {
902  clear();
903  }
904 
905  void clear()
906  {
907  pt = -1;
908  marker = false;
909  seq = 0;
910  ssrc = 0;
911  ts = 0;
912  }
913 
914  virtual void initForDocumenting()
915  {
916  clear();
917  pt = 0;
918  marker = false;
919  seq = 123;
920  ssrc = 12345678;
921  ts = 87654321;
922  }
923  };
924 
925  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const RtpHeader& p)
926  {
927  if(p.pt != -1)
928  {
929  j = nlohmann::json{
930  TOJSON_IMPL(pt),
931  TOJSON_IMPL(marker),
932  TOJSON_IMPL(seq),
933  TOJSON_IMPL(ssrc),
934  TOJSON_IMPL(ts)
935  };
936  }
937  }
938  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, RtpHeader& p)
939  {
940  p.clear();
941  getOptional<int>("pt", p.pt, j, -1);
942  getOptional<bool>("marker", p.marker, j, false);
943  getOptional<uint16_t>("seq", p.seq, j, 0);
944  getOptional<uint32_t>("ssrc", p.ssrc, j, 0);
945  getOptional<uint32_t>("ts", p.ts, j, 0);
946  }

963  public:
967  typedef enum
968  {
970  bptUndefined = 0,
971

974 
976  bptJsonTextUtf8 = 2,
977 
979  bptAppBinary = 3,
980 
982  bptEngageBinaryHumanBiometrics = 4

986  size_t size;
987

1018  }

1278  class Location : public ConfigurationObjectBase
1279  {
1280  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
1281  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(Location)
1282 
1283  public:
1284  constexpr static double INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE = -999.999;
1285 
1287  uint32_t ts;
1288 
1290  double latitude;
1291 
1293  double longitude;
1294 
1296  double altitude;
1297 
1299  double direction;
1300 
1302  double speed;
1303 
1304  Location()
1305  {
1306  clear();
1307  }
1308 
1309  void clear()
1310  {
1311  ts = 0;
1312  latitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1313  longitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1314  altitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1315  direction = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1316  speed = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1317  }
1318 
1319  virtual void initForDocumenting()
1320  {
1321  clear();
1322 
1323  ts = 123456;
1324  latitude = 123.456;
1325  longitude = 456.789;
1326  altitude = 123;
1327  direction = 1;
1328  speed = 1234;
1329  }
1330  };

1332  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Location& p)
1333  {
1334  if(p.latitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE && p.longitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE)
1335  {
1336  j = nlohmann::json{
1337  TOJSON_IMPL(latitude),
1338  TOJSON_IMPL(longitude),
1339  };
1340 
1341  if(p.ts != 0) j["ts"] = p.ts;
1342  if(p.altitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["altitude"] = p.altitude;
1343  if(p.speed != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["speed"] = p.speed;
1344  if(p.direction != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["direction"] = p.direction;
1345  }
1346  }

1348  {
1349  p.clear();
1350  getOptional<uint32_t>("ts", p.ts, j, 0);
1351  j.at("latitude").get_to(p.latitude);
1352  j.at("longitude").get_to(p.longitude);
1353  getOptional<double>("altitude", p.altitude, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1354  getOptional<double>("direction", p.direction, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1355  getOptional<double>("speed", p.speed, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1356  }

2067  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(Rallypoint)
2075  class Rallypoint : public ConfigurationObjectBase
2076  {
2077  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
2078  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(Rallypoint)
2079 
2080  public:
2081 
2086  NetworkAddress host;
2087 
2099  std::string certificate;
2100 
2112  std::string certificateKey;
2113 
2117  bool verifyPeer;
2118 
2122  bool allowSelfSignedCertificate;
2123 
2127  std::vector<std::string> caCertificates;
2128 
2132  int transactionTimeoutMs;
2133 
2137  bool disableMessageSigning;
2138 
2140  int connectionTimeoutSecs;
2141 
2142  Rallypoint()
2143  {
2144  clear();
2145  }
2146 
2147  void clear()
2148  {
2149  host.clear();
2150  certificate.clear();
2151  certificateKey.clear();
2152  caCertificates.clear();
2153  verifyPeer = false;
2154  transactionTimeoutMs = 5000;
2155  disableMessageSigning = false;
2156  connectionTimeoutSecs = 5;
2157  }
2158 
2159  bool matches(const Rallypoint& other)
2160  {
2161  if(!host.matches(other.host))
2162  {
2163  return false;
2164  }
2165 
2166  if(certificate.compare(other.certificate) != 0)
2167  {
2168  return false;
2169  }
2170 
2171  if(certificateKey.compare(other.certificateKey) != 0)
2172  {
2173  return false;
2174  }
2175 
2176  if(verifyPeer != other.verifyPeer)
2177  {
2178  return false;
2179  }
2180 
2181  if(allowSelfSignedCertificate != other.allowSelfSignedCertificate)
2182  {
2183  return false;
2184  }
2185 
2186  if(caCertificates.size() != other.caCertificates.size())
2187  {
2188  return false;
2189  }
2190 
2191  for(size_t x = 0; x < caCertificates.size(); x++)
2192  {
2193  bool found = false;
2194 
2195  for(size_t y = 0; y < other.caCertificates.size(); y++)
2196  {
2197  if(caCertificates[x].compare(other.caCertificates[y]) == 0)
2198  {
2199  found = true;
2200  break;
2201  }
2202  }
2203 
2204  if(!found)
2205  {
2206  return false;
2207  }
2208  }
2209 
2210  if(transactionTimeoutMs != other.transactionTimeoutMs)
2211  {
2212  return false;
2213  }
2214 
2215  if(disableMessageSigning != other.disableMessageSigning)
2216  {
2217  return false;
2218  }
2219 
2220  return true;
2221  }
2222  };
2223 
2224  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Rallypoint& p)
2225  {
2226  j = nlohmann::json{
2227  TOJSON_IMPL(host),
2228  TOJSON_IMPL(certificate),
2229  TOJSON_IMPL(certificateKey),
2230  TOJSON_IMPL(verifyPeer),
2231  TOJSON_IMPL(allowSelfSignedCertificate),
2232  TOJSON_IMPL(caCertificates),
2233  TOJSON_IMPL(transactionTimeoutMs),
2234  TOJSON_IMPL(disableMessageSigning),
2235  TOJSON_IMPL(connectionTimeoutSecs)
2236  };
2237  }
2238 
2239  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Rallypoint& p)
2240  {
2241  p.clear();
2242  j.at("host").get_to(p.host);
2243  getOptional("certificate", p.certificate, j);
2244  getOptional("certificateKey", p.certificateKey, j);
2245  getOptional<bool>("verifyPeer", p.verifyPeer, j, false);
2246  getOptional<bool>("allowSelfSignedCertificate", p.allowSelfSignedCertificate, j, true);
2247  getOptional<std::vector<std::string>>("caCertificates", p.caCertificates, j);
2248  getOptional<int>("transactionTimeoutMs", p.transactionTimeoutMs, j, 5000);
2249  getOptional<bool>("disableMessageSigning", p.disableMessageSigning, j, false);

3925 
3926  // TODO: need a better way to indicate whether rtpProfile is present
3927  if(p._wasDeserialized_rtpProfile || p.isDocumenting())
3928  {
3929  j["rtpProfile"] = p.rtpProfile;
3930  }
3931

3933  {
3934  j["rallypointCluster"] = p.rallypointCluster;
3935  j["rallypoints"] = p.rallypoints;
3936  }
3937  else
3938  {

3940  if(!p.rallypointCluster.rallypoints.empty())
3941  {
3942  j["rallypointCluster"] = p.rallypointCluster;
3943  }
3944  else if(!p.rallypoints.empty())
3945  {
3946  j["rallypoints"] = p.rallypoints;
3947  }
3948  }

3950  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Group& p)
3951  {

3953  j.at("type").get_to(p.type);
3954  getOptional<Group::BridgingOpMode_t>("bom", p.bom, j, Group::BridgingOpMode_t::bomRaw);
3955  j.at("id").get_to(p.id);
3956  getOptional<std::string>("name", p.name, j);
3957  getOptional<std::string>("interfaceName", p.interfaceName, j);
3958  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("rx", p.rx, j);
3959  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("tx", p.tx, j);
3960  getOptional<NetworkTxOptions>("txOptions", p.txOptions, j);
3961  getOptional<std::string>("cryptoPassword", p.cryptoPassword, j);
3962  getOptional<std::string>("alias", p.alias, j);
3963  getOptional<TxAudio>("txAudio", p.txAudio, j);
3964  getOptional<Presence>("presence", p.presence, j);
3965  getOptional<std::vector<Rallypoint>>("rallypoints", p.rallypoints, j);
3966  getOptional<RallypointCluster>("rallypointCluster", p.rallypointCluster, j);
3967  getOptional<Audio>("audio", p.audio, j);
3968  getOptional<GroupTimeline>("timeline", p.timeline, j);
3969  getOptional<bool>("blockAdvertising", p.blockAdvertising, j, false);
3970  getOptional<std::string>("source", p.source, j);
3971  getOptional<int>("maxRxSecs", p.maxRxSecs, j, 0);
3972  getOptional<bool>("enableMulticastFailover", p.enableMulticastFailover, j, false);
3973  getOptional<int>("multicastFailoverSecs", p.multicastFailoverSecs, j, 10);
3974  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("rtcpPresenceRx", p.rtcpPresenceRx, j);
3975  getOptional<bool>("enableRxVad", p.enableRxVad, j, false);
3976  getOptional<std::vector<std::string>>("presenceGroupAffinities", p.presenceGroupAffinities, j);
3977  getOptional<bool>("disablePacketEvents", p.disablePacketEvents, j, false);

5839  TOJSON_IMPL(name),
5840  TOJSON_IMPL(file)
5841  };
5842 
5843  if(!p.configuration.empty())
5844  {
5845  j["configuration"] = p.configuration;
5846  }
5847  }
5848  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, ExternalModule& p)
5849  {
5850  p.clear();
5851  getOptional<std::string>("name", p.name, j, EMPTY_STRING);
5852  getOptional<std::string>("file", p.file, j, EMPTY_STRING);
5853 
5854  try
5855  {
5856  p.configuration = j.at("configuration");
5857  }
5858  catch(...)
5859  {
5860  p.configuration.clear();
5861  }
5862  }
